WEBVTT

00:07.750 --> 00:10.820
- [device vibrating]
- [Lily] Oh, my God,
that feels so good.

00:11.020 --> 00:13.200
Oh, that's so good.

00:13.400 --> 00:15.200
Deeper, baby. Go deeper.

00:15.400 --> 00:18.040
[Nick] I don't want to hurt you.
I don't think you can handle it.

00:18.240 --> 00:21.960
[Lily] Oh, I can handle it.
Oh, I need it now.

00:22.160 --> 00:24.800
Oh, yeah. Oh! Yeah, that's
the spot, that's the spot.

00:25.000 --> 00:26.380
That's the spot right there,
right there, right there.

00:26.580 --> 00:28.680
Oh, yes, yes.

00:28.870 --> 00:30.340
Every Thanksgiving,
without fail,

00:30.540 --> 00:32.430
I hurt my back volunteering.

00:32.630 --> 00:35.970
This time, it was a box
of canned yams that got me.

00:36.170 --> 00:38.600
I told you,
the correct way to lift a box

00:38.800 --> 00:41.100
is with your legs, Diaz,
not your back.

00:41.300 --> 00:43.360
Thankfully,
this year wasn't so bad

00:43.560 --> 00:46.360
because my sweet boyfriend did
most of the heavy lifting.

00:46.560 --> 00:48.280
- [vibrating stops]
- Whoa.

00:48.480 --> 00:50.760
Call me boyfriend again.

00:52.880 --> 00:55.090
- Okay, boyfriend.
- [chuckles]

00:58.510 --> 01:01.290
- [phone chimes]
- [Nick groans]
- Aw, really?

01:01.490 --> 01:02.960
Hey, if that's Jorge,

01:03.160 --> 01:04.880
you tell him for the final time
I'm not donating my Tevas.

01:05.080 --> 01:06.420
They're coming back
into fashion,

01:06.620 --> 01:08.610
- and I'm gonna be
ahead of the trend.
- [laughs]

01:10.270 --> 01:13.090
Oh, it's-it's Santiago
texting me Happy Thanksgiving.

01:13.290 --> 01:14.320
Oh, that's nice.

01:15.360 --> 01:16.810
Are you sure you're okay?

01:17.010 --> 01:20.440
With Santi and I being friends?

01:20.630 --> 01:23.310
- Well, I trust my girlfriend.
- Yeah.

01:23.510 --> 01:26.110
- Call me girlfriend again.
- Okay, girlfriend.

01:26.310 --> 01:28.230
And the fact that
you tell me about it every time

01:28.430 --> 01:29.900
makes me trust you even more.

01:30.100 --> 01:33.990
- You do tell me
every time, though, right?
- Of course.

01:34.190 --> 01:36.450
He left me one voice mail,
and we text every now and then.

01:36.650 --> 01:39.120
Okay, then I'm only
three percent bothered by it.

01:39.320 --> 01:42.120
Oh, wow,
that's 97% cool of you.

01:42.320 --> 01:45.640
- Mm, math. Sexy.
- Mm.

01:46.850 --> 01:48.600
23 x 3.

01:50.440 --> 01:53.180
- [laughs]
- [chuckles, moans]

01:53.380 --> 01:55.320
♪ ♪

01:57.860 --> 02:01.390
[Henry] And Happy Thanksgiving
to you, too.

02:01.590 --> 02:03.810
- Oh!
- [gasps] Wow.

02:04.010 --> 02:05.400
Hey, Beatriz, Jorge!

02:05.600 --> 02:07.690
- Hey!
- Happy Thanksgiving!
- Happy Thanksgiving.

02:07.890 --> 02:10.230
- You're right on time.
- Well, put us to work, <i>jefe.</i>

02:10.430 --> 02:13.030
Oh, and don't hold back, because
I need to regain my muscle mass

02:13.230 --> 02:15.280
from all the months
of lounging on the beach.

02:15.480 --> 02:17.780
- Oh.
- Right, rub it in, okay.

02:17.980 --> 02:20.410
[laughs] It's actually
my handsome vice <i>jefe</i>

02:20.610 --> 02:21.950
that is in charge of
handing out the jobs today,

02:22.150 --> 02:23.620
and I trust him completely

02:23.820 --> 02:26.880
to assign your skills
where they are best suited.

02:27.080 --> 02:28.500
[whispers] You'll be
in the kitchen.

02:28.700 --> 02:31.050
I was gonna say kitchen.

02:31.250 --> 02:32.760
Let me do my job.

02:32.960 --> 02:35.340
Vice <i>jefe</i> isn't just
a ceremonial title, Jorge.

02:35.540 --> 02:38.760
- Okay. This way. Come on.
- Okay.

02:38.960 --> 02:40.610
[Henry] I love you.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.730
Hola, beautiful.

02:48.930 --> 02:51.230
- Laz! Hey, stud.
- [laughs]

02:51.430 --> 02:53.240
So are those gently used clothes
in your bag,

02:53.440 --> 02:54.490
or are you just happy to see me?

02:54.690 --> 02:56.280
- Both. [laughs]
- Okay.

02:56.480 --> 02:58.200
What are you and Santiago up to
for the holiday?

02:58.400 --> 03:00.540
Oh, we're ordering
some pizza from Burnside.

03:00.730 --> 03:02.950
Bur... That's not even
a good pizza place.

03:03.150 --> 03:06.830
Ah, a little pineapple
and pepperoni, it's okay.

03:07.030 --> 03:08.290
Wait, really?

03:08.490 --> 03:11.250
Thanksgiving's been, uh,
sort of cancelled

03:11.450 --> 03:12.760
ever since my wife passed.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.340
Okay, no, no, no, no, no.

03:14.540 --> 03:15.970
Two beautiful men,
sad and alone

03:16.170 --> 03:18.180
on Thanksgiving,
eating shitty pizza...

03:18.380 --> 03:19.350
Not on my watch.

03:19.540 --> 03:20.930
I think I'm gonna have to insist
that you come

03:21.130 --> 03:23.310
to the Diaz house for
a proper Thanksgiving dinner.

03:23.510 --> 03:25.770
- Look, that's very generous...
- No, it's not generous.

03:25.970 --> 03:28.940
It is selfish.
I need some eye candy. Help me.

03:29.140 --> 03:31.610
Yeah. Exactly.

03:31.810 --> 03:33.820
- [laughs]
- Come on.

03:34.020 --> 03:35.400
Santi and Lily are friends now,
right?

03:35.600 --> 03:37.530
- It's all good.
- I'll tell you what,

03:37.730 --> 03:39.200
we'll think about it.

03:39.400 --> 03:40.320
Fair enough?

03:40.520 --> 03:42.490
You, thinking about me?

03:42.690 --> 03:43.840
I don't hate it.

03:54.020 --> 03:55.630
What's this?

03:55.830 --> 03:59.300
Ah, shit, you weren't
supposed to see that.

03:59.500 --> 04:00.760
Is this for me?

04:00.960 --> 04:02.850
Yes, but it's for later.

04:03.050 --> 04:05.850
I'm sorry,
but once you discover a gift,

04:06.050 --> 04:07.530
you got to open it,
them's the rules.

04:10.450 --> 04:11.610
[gasps]

04:11.810 --> 04:14.440
My first official lab coat.

04:14.640 --> 04:15.960
Thank you.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.710
Dr. Sol Perez.

04:20.760 --> 04:23.410
Who's laughing now,
<i>tía</i> Carmela? MD, baby!

04:23.610 --> 04:25.490
[laughs] That's right.

04:25.690 --> 04:27.120
Why are we mad at <i>tía</i> Carmela?

04:27.320 --> 04:30.080
[groans] She's the one
that's always so concerned about

04:30.280 --> 04:32.500
my life amounting to nothing
because I'm different.

04:32.700 --> 04:35.000
So, tonight, I'm gonna rub this
in her face.

04:35.200 --> 04:36.760
Well, screw her.

04:36.960 --> 04:38.720
Isn't she some life coach
with no clients?

04:38.920 --> 04:40.260
Whoa.

04:40.460 --> 04:42.090
You can't talk about my family
like that.

04:42.290 --> 04:43.470
You just said
you don't like her.

04:43.670 --> 04:45.430
Yeah, I can talk crap.
You can't.

04:45.630 --> 04:47.270
I'm sorry.

04:47.470 --> 04:49.980
I was really only
trying to be supportive.

04:50.180 --> 04:51.870
I know. It's okay.

04:53.500 --> 04:55.330
But don't do it again.

05:03.470 --> 05:05.740
- [sighs]
- What's up, Diaz?

05:05.940 --> 05:09.850
Mm, no, I'm just browsing houses
and looking at prices.

05:10.930 --> 05:12.460
How much do you think
I could sell my hair for?

05:12.660 --> 05:15.090
120 K? 'Cause that's just
the down payment.

05:15.290 --> 05:17.420
Whoa, okay, okay,
stop spiraling.

05:17.620 --> 05:20.130
Look at this dream house.

05:20.330 --> 05:21.800
- Three bedrooms.
- [Nick] Ooh.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.760
- Hello, claw-foot tub.
- Ooh.

05:24.960 --> 05:26.510
Ooh, what's up,
beautiful kitchen?

05:26.710 --> 05:28.270
But the problem is,

05:28.470 --> 05:30.020
I'm never gonna be able
to afford it.

05:30.220 --> 05:32.440
I ran the numbers. It's bad.

05:32.640 --> 05:34.560
Well, I can definitely see you
in that tub.

05:34.760 --> 05:37.070
- Don't make it worse.
- [laughs]

05:37.270 --> 05:39.690
Okay, well,
how about I make it better?

05:39.890 --> 05:43.530
- Why don't I help you buy it?
- What?

05:43.730 --> 05:45.490
Yeah, you know,
I could help you pay for it.

05:45.690 --> 05:46.950
Give you money
for the down payment.

05:47.150 --> 05:49.040
Help you with the monthlies.
No sweat.

05:49.240 --> 05:51.120
I'm sorry, we're talking about
a house here.

05:51.320 --> 05:53.580
- Not a steak dinner.
- I know, I know,

05:53.780 --> 05:55.330
and I've been
thinking about this a lot.

05:55.530 --> 05:58.130
And I know
we're pretty early on, but...

05:58.330 --> 06:00.520
this is pretty great
right now, isn't it?

06:01.940 --> 06:04.010
Yeah. It is.

06:04.210 --> 06:07.950
Okay, so, in success, we will be
living in that house together.

06:09.110 --> 06:11.310
Let me help you out. Come on.

06:11.510 --> 06:13.850
I have lots of money.
I-I have stocks and bonds.

06:14.050 --> 06:16.270
And a trust and gold
in a vault in Switzerland.

06:16.470 --> 06:17.860
This T-shirt cost me $200.

06:18.060 --> 06:20.360
[laughs]

06:20.560 --> 06:21.820
That's so generous,

06:22.020 --> 06:24.910
but I don't think
I'm comfortable with that.

06:25.110 --> 06:26.570
Okay, fair enough.

06:26.770 --> 06:29.950
But the offer is still good,
if you change your mind.

06:30.150 --> 06:32.680
Thank you.
That's so sweet.

06:33.720 --> 06:35.580
Big day.
Lots of choices.

06:35.780 --> 06:37.750
- Mm-hmm.
- Now we can go with cheese.

06:37.950 --> 06:39.130
For sure. Right?

06:39.330 --> 06:41.760
But I'm thinking,
I get a meat lover's for me,

06:41.960 --> 06:43.300
get a veggie pizza for you,

06:43.500 --> 06:45.090
then I get a Hawaiian pizza
for the table.

06:45.290 --> 06:47.930
That sounds like something we
should be thankful for, right?

06:48.130 --> 06:49.470
- Question.
- Mm-hmm?

06:49.670 --> 06:50.930
How would you feel about

06:51.130 --> 06:54.240
a real Thanksgiving dinner
tonight, instead of pizza?

06:55.290 --> 06:56.730
Uh, dubious, why?

06:56.930 --> 06:58.860
[clears throat] Okay.

06:59.060 --> 07:00.320
You're not gonna like this
at first,

07:00.520 --> 07:01.530
and when I tell you
the whole plan,

07:01.730 --> 07:02.780
you're gonna like it even less,

07:02.980 --> 07:04.550
but hear me out.

07:05.710 --> 07:06.910
All right.

07:07.110 --> 07:09.450
I saw Gladys today. Mmm.

07:09.650 --> 07:12.240
And we've been invited
to the Diaz's house

07:12.440 --> 07:14.510
for Thanksgiving dinner.
I think we should go.

07:15.850 --> 07:18.100
- [sucks teeth] Okay.
- 'Cause...

07:19.310 --> 07:21.920
Oh. Oh.

07:22.120 --> 07:23.420
I didn't expect that
to be your response.

07:23.620 --> 07:24.970
Whew. [laughs] Okay.

07:25.170 --> 07:26.720
I mean, I got a whole bunch of
arguments worked out.

07:26.920 --> 07:27.720
I mean, you want to hear them?

07:27.920 --> 07:30.010
No. [laughs]

07:30.210 --> 07:31.640
Lily and I have been texting
a little bit, you know,

07:31.840 --> 07:34.270
but, uh, we haven't really
talked since her birthday.

07:34.470 --> 07:37.480
- Might be nice to catch up.
- Really?

07:37.680 --> 07:39.900
Yeah, really. As friends.

07:40.100 --> 07:42.690
Oh. [laughs]

07:42.890 --> 07:44.860
- Okay.
- We can't we be friends?

07:45.060 --> 07:47.250
Okay, buddy. Okay.
Friends, huh?

07:49.840 --> 07:51.740
Is everyone seeing
what I'm seeing right now?

07:51.940 --> 07:53.240
Oh, was it a raccoon?

07:53.440 --> 07:54.620
Because I saw
on the Nextdoor app

07:54.820 --> 07:56.210
there's a raccoon going around
tipping over

07:56.400 --> 07:58.500
people's turkey fryers with
his freaky little human hands.

07:58.700 --> 08:00.580
- [laughs]
- No, Nick. Not a raccoon.

08:00.780 --> 08:02.840
Us. The four of us.

08:03.040 --> 08:05.090
Walking to Thanksgiving
together,

08:05.290 --> 08:07.840
as couples, together. Hello!

08:08.040 --> 08:10.340
We're basically
like a quad couple now.

08:10.540 --> 08:13.180
- Aw.
- That's kind of cute, babe.
- Yeah. Thanks.

08:13.380 --> 08:15.470
Hey, your family finally
gets to be right about me

08:15.670 --> 08:16.810
being the boyfriend,
except this time,

08:17.010 --> 08:18.640
I'm Lily's for-real boyfriend

08:18.840 --> 08:21.150
- and not your fake, secret one.
- That's right.

08:21.350 --> 08:22.610
I have to admit,

08:22.810 --> 08:25.280
I did have my concerns
about you two.

08:25.480 --> 08:28.780
You had your concerns?
You were 100% freaked out.

08:28.980 --> 08:30.820
- I freaked out. I freaked out.
- [laughter]

08:31.020 --> 08:34.870
But it's my rakish best friend
and my starry-eyed sister.

08:35.070 --> 08:36.790
Ooh, rakish? Well, hey, listen,

08:36.990 --> 08:38.460
you did have cause
to be concerned.

08:38.660 --> 08:40.670
[laughs] Well,
the last few months have

08:40.870 --> 08:42.790
been incredible, and
this isn't even the best part.

08:42.990 --> 08:44.590
This is only the beginning.
I mean, think about it.

08:44.790 --> 08:46.170
Vacations in Baja,

08:46.370 --> 08:49.340
raising our incredibly
good-looking children together.

08:49.540 --> 08:52.140
[gasps] Wait, Lil,
are we gonna be neighbors?

08:52.340 --> 08:53.430
I think we should be neighbors.

08:53.630 --> 08:54.930
Oh, my God, we'll be together
forever, then.

08:55.130 --> 08:56.720
This is, like,
the best day ever.

08:56.920 --> 08:59.140
I swear, like, it's like
what we've been dreaming about

08:59.340 --> 09:01.400
- our whole lives. I love you.
- Oh, come on.

09:01.590 --> 09:03.110
Oh, my God, I love you guys.
This is so cute.

09:03.310 --> 09:05.070
[quiet chatter]

09:05.270 --> 09:06.480
- Hey, <i>¡primos!</i>
- Hey!

09:06.680 --> 09:07.900
- Wait, don't wrinkle me.
- [grunting]

09:08.100 --> 09:09.780
- Ah.
- Ah!

09:09.980 --> 09:12.320
- Oh, watch the spine, watch
the spine, watch the spine.
- Sorry.

09:12.520 --> 09:14.700
I got to make up for all
the months I don't see you guys.

09:14.900 --> 09:16.290
Ah, I know, we miss you, too.

09:16.480 --> 09:18.160
Bring it in, Chuey.
Do what you got to do.

09:18.360 --> 09:20.210
<i>¡Órale!</i> [grunts]

09:20.410 --> 09:21.790
- [laughter]
- I know. I know.

09:21.990 --> 09:23.790
How is L.A.?
How is the food truck going?

09:23.990 --> 09:25.420
Oh, so good.

09:25.620 --> 09:27.670
I got into a bit of a turf war
with a taco truck in K-Town,

09:27.870 --> 09:29.880
but I made an offer
they couldn't refuse.

09:30.080 --> 09:31.840
What was the offer?

09:32.040 --> 09:33.300
To alternate days, there's
plenty of room for everybody.

09:33.500 --> 09:35.720
- Oh, okay.
- Except that raw garlic
juice truck.

09:35.920 --> 09:37.810
- [groans] Fuck them.
- [laughs]

09:38.010 --> 09:40.270
Hey, Henry, you got a sec?

09:40.470 --> 09:42.350
Oh, uh, of course,
Miles, what's up?

09:42.550 --> 09:43.650
I need a little advice,

09:43.850 --> 09:45.230
since everyone in the family
loves you.

09:45.430 --> 09:47.920
'Tis true.
How can I help?

09:48.960 --> 09:51.030
I know how important
family is to Sol,

09:51.230 --> 09:53.160
and I want to do this right.

09:53.360 --> 09:57.490
I kind of put my foot in it
earlier, and I was thinking,

09:57.690 --> 09:59.950
if there are rules,
you would know them.

10:00.150 --> 10:01.370
I got you, Doc.

10:01.570 --> 10:03.750
I created a Diaz family wiki.

10:03.950 --> 10:07.340
Okay, so, first rule is, you
don't talk shit about family.

10:07.540 --> 10:09.130
You're not actually family.

10:09.330 --> 10:10.760
Yeah, learned that one
the hard way this morning.

10:10.960 --> 10:12.970
Rookie move. You should've
come to me sooner.

10:13.170 --> 10:16.050
When someone offers you seconds,
always say yes.

10:16.250 --> 10:17.810
Never comment
on Alberto's tattoo.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.810
His father's not over it.

10:20.010 --> 10:22.890
Do not eat the mole
if <i>tía</i> Anita made it.

10:23.090 --> 10:24.400
You know what?
There's a lot.

10:24.590 --> 10:26.690
I-I'm just gonna AirDrop these.

10:26.890 --> 10:28.860
- There you go.
- Okay.

10:29.060 --> 10:31.000
[clears throat]

10:32.130 --> 10:34.110
Wow, it's still downloading.

10:34.310 --> 10:35.800
[exhales sharply]

10:37.470 --> 10:39.260
Oh. Oh.

10:40.680 --> 10:42.710
[softly] Oh, come on.

10:42.900 --> 10:46.210
Lil, you really need to upgrade
your phone. It's always dying.

10:46.410 --> 10:48.460
Going through Zillow nonstop
doesn't help the battery life.

10:48.660 --> 10:52.210
Well, take a break from that
and come get wine drunk with me,

10:52.410 --> 10:54.800
'cause I heard <i>tía</i> Carmela's
laugh and my shoulders...

10:55.000 --> 10:56.010
[whispers] ...they're
in my ears.

10:56.210 --> 10:57.340
- Yes. Let's go.
- [laughs]

10:57.540 --> 10:59.350
Wait.

10:59.550 --> 11:01.390
- Oh, can I have
some more of this, please?
- [Sol] Mm-hmm.

11:01.590 --> 11:03.640
- [Lily] Feels really funny,
I know.
- [Sol laughs]

11:03.840 --> 11:05.980
Hey, Sol,
give me some of your...

11:06.180 --> 11:08.120
[indistinct chatter]

11:09.920 --> 11:11.480
- I say we toss it. What?
- Gladys!

11:11.680 --> 11:12.740
Not in, like, an obvious way.
She doesn't have to know.

11:12.930 --> 11:14.700
What's going on?

11:14.890 --> 11:17.200
Your <i>mami</i> is too polite
and insists on

11:17.400 --> 11:19.700
putting <i>tía</i> Anita's
shitty mole on the table.

11:19.900 --> 11:21.950
Am I the only one that remembers
what happened last year?

11:22.150 --> 11:23.540
- No.
- Too many people,
not enough toilets.

11:23.740 --> 11:25.580
- Ooh.
- Honestly, I'm surprised

11:25.780 --> 11:26.960
you didn't have to,
like, burn the house down.

11:27.160 --> 11:28.790
- [laughter]
- Okay, look, I'll just,

11:28.990 --> 11:31.000
I'll just put it right here
with the lid on.

11:31.200 --> 11:32.840
Okay. Wuss.

11:33.040 --> 11:36.090
Uh, I haven't seen <i>abuelo</i> yet
tonight.

11:36.290 --> 11:37.380
Is everything okay?

11:37.580 --> 11:39.780
Yes, uh, fine, fine.

11:41.660 --> 11:44.270
Okay, well, he hasn't been
sleeping well lately,

11:44.470 --> 11:46.890
but that happens sometimes.

11:47.090 --> 11:48.310
Makes the dementia worse?

11:48.510 --> 11:50.230
Well, yes, a little bit,

11:50.430 --> 11:52.570
but it's nothing
we can't handle, <i>familia.</i>

11:52.770 --> 11:54.070
Well, we'll keep an eye out.

11:54.270 --> 11:55.650
He may mistake you
for someone else,

11:55.850 --> 11:57.400
but as long as
that person is attractive,

11:57.600 --> 11:59.780
- I'm good with it.
- [laughter]

11:59.980 --> 12:01.780
Happy gobble, gobble day!

12:01.980 --> 12:03.450
Hi, <i>¡abuelito!</i>

12:03.650 --> 12:06.620
What are all my favorite people
doing hiding out in here?

12:06.820 --> 12:10.080
- Look at you. You look cute.
- [singsongy] <i>Abuelito...</i>

12:10.280 --> 12:12.210
- [overlapping chatter]
- Let's go. Turn up the music.

12:12.410 --> 12:14.050
Oh, the party's here!

12:14.250 --> 12:16.230
[sighs]

12:20.150 --> 12:21.510
I don't know
why you keep putting that on,

12:21.710 --> 12:22.810
when it's just gonna
come right off.

12:23.000 --> 12:24.640
You should just put it
directly on me.

