25:51.020 --> 25:52.910
Want to go kick some ass
at games together?

25:53.110 --> 25:54.160
Yes.

25:54.360 --> 25:55.550
[both laugh]

25:57.760 --> 25:59.050
Oh.

26:01.430 --> 26:04.520
- Oh, look at that,
we're on the same team.
- Aw!

26:07.230 --> 26:09.020
- Oh. Hmm.
- Oh.

26:10.060 --> 26:13.180
Oh, I am so sorry
that Santiago's on your team.

26:13.380 --> 26:15.720
I picked names
out of a bowl, I swear.

26:15.920 --> 26:18.100
The universe is using me
as an instrument of its fuckery.

26:18.300 --> 26:20.060
- It's fine. Yeah.
- Yeah, absolutely.

26:20.260 --> 26:21.770
Well, I could redo the teams.

26:21.970 --> 26:23.560
- Great.
- No, it'll just be weirder.

26:23.760 --> 26:25.400
- We're all adults here.
- Totally.

26:25.600 --> 26:27.820
Good, 'cause I wasn't
gonna redo the teams.

26:28.020 --> 26:30.440
- [laughs]
- [clears throat]

26:30.640 --> 26:32.420
- Okay.
- Hmm.

26:33.420 --> 26:36.570
[Chuey] Uh, Juanes.
No, Los Tigres del Norte!

26:36.770 --> 26:39.200
- Electric.
- Yeah.

26:39.400 --> 26:43.620
<i>- Breakin' 2: Electric Boogaloo!</i>
- Yeah. You go! Yes!

26:43.820 --> 26:46.250
Yes, yes, yes! [cheering]

26:46.450 --> 26:48.380
Sol, come on.

26:48.580 --> 26:50.260
Why are you so mad at me?
I was standing up for you.

26:50.450 --> 26:51.510
Because I didn't ask you to
do that.

26:51.710 --> 26:53.300
- [sighs]
- In fact, I distinctly recall

26:53.500 --> 26:54.720
asking you to do the opposite.

26:54.920 --> 26:57.100
Okay, look,
I understand you're upset,

26:57.290 --> 26:58.680
and I want to apologize, but...

26:58.880 --> 27:01.350
[scoffing] But?

27:01.550 --> 27:03.730
But I'm not sorry.

27:03.930 --> 27:06.310
I-I don't regret
what I said to <i>tía</i> Carmela.

27:06.510 --> 27:08.440
Not one bit.
Usually, I back down.

27:08.640 --> 27:11.280
I-I try to let things go,
but I am done letting her

27:11.480 --> 27:13.090
treat you that way
without any consequence.

27:15.090 --> 27:16.990
[group] Movie! Six words!

27:17.190 --> 27:19.280
And were you thinking
about consequences

27:19.480 --> 27:22.450
when you decided to stir the pot
and drive her to tears?

27:22.650 --> 27:23.830
Now she's gone
full-blown drama queen.

27:24.030 --> 27:25.250
<i>The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo?</i>

27:25.450 --> 27:27.130
<i>¿Qué?</i>

27:27.320 --> 27:29.040
How are Carmelas's dramatics

27:29.240 --> 27:32.050
a-and lack of boundaries
your responsibility?

27:32.250 --> 27:33.550
She needs to own her behavior.

27:33.750 --> 27:36.130
Oh, uh, second word, sunshine.

27:36.330 --> 27:38.340
- Uh, uh, <i>You Are My Sunshine?</i>
- [imitates buzzer] That's
four words,

27:38.540 --> 27:39.800
and sunshine is the second word.

27:40.000 --> 27:41.430
"You Are the Sunshine
of My Life"?

27:41.630 --> 27:43.470
<i>- Tía</i> Anita,
that's not even a movie!
- Ay.

27:43.670 --> 27:44.930
Get your head in the game, <i>¡tía!</i>

27:45.130 --> 27:46.810
- [Anita] <i>Ay, dale, dale, dale.</i>
- Look.

27:47.010 --> 27:49.480
Maybe we all wish <i>tía</i> Carmela
would change her ways,

27:49.680 --> 27:51.190
but this is gonna domino-effect

27:51.390 --> 27:53.230
until everyone in my family
is suffering.

27:53.430 --> 27:54.780
Ooh, dusting off, dusting off?

27:54.980 --> 27:55.990
Well, maybe
your family needs to learn

27:56.190 --> 27:57.110
how to deal with that
differently,

27:57.310 --> 27:58.410
because it's not cool,

27:58.610 --> 28:00.200
and I'm gonna stand up
for the person I love.

28:00.400 --> 28:02.120
Oh, you're bald.
You're bald.

28:02.320 --> 28:03.660
- You're bold.
- Mind.

28:03.860 --> 28:05.290
<i>Eternal Sunshine</i>
<i>of the Spotless Mind.</i>

28:05.490 --> 28:08.500
- Yes!
- [cheering]

28:08.700 --> 28:10.500
[laughter]

28:10.700 --> 28:12.500
<i>Vamos a ganar, a ganar.</i>

28:12.700 --> 28:14.210
- <i>Vamos a ganar. ¡Vamos!</i>
- [whooping]

28:14.410 --> 28:15.920
- We got this. We got this.
- Yes, yes, yes, yes. Let's go.

28:16.120 --> 28:17.480
- Uh, film. Film.
- Movie.

28:18.230 --> 28:20.010
- Uh, one word.
- One word. We got this.
- One word.

28:20.210 --> 28:21.300
- [Nick] Yeah. Yeah.
- [Jorge Sr.] Here we go.

28:21.500 --> 28:23.970
- Here we go. <i>Fargo? Jaws?</i>
- Easy.

28:24.170 --> 28:25.520
- <i>Annie. Annie.</i>
- Uh, ooh, <i>Marry Poppins.</i>

28:25.720 --> 28:26.520
Dancing.

28:26.720 --> 28:28.850
One word. One word. Dancing.

28:29.050 --> 28:31.150
Uh, uh, uh, oh, oh, oh!
Oh, <i>Sex and the City.</i>

28:31.350 --> 28:33.820
[stammers] <i>Paddington 2.</i>
<i>Paddington 2.</i>

28:34.020 --> 28:34.980
[Jorge Sr.] Dude, dude,
dude, one word.

28:35.180 --> 28:36.530
You can just say <i>Paddington.</i>

28:36.730 --> 28:37.780
- Is it <i>Paddington?</i>
- Is it <i>Paddington?</i>

28:37.980 --> 28:39.200
No, no, no!
It's not <i>Paddington.</i>

28:39.400 --> 28:41.380
Okay, fresh start, fresh start.

28:44.090 --> 28:45.330
[imitates retching]

28:45.530 --> 28:46.700
- <i>Cinderella! Cinderella.</i>
- Yes, Santi!

28:46.900 --> 28:48.580
- Go, Santi, yes, yes!
- That was it?

28:48.780 --> 28:49.960
- Yes!
- What was that?

28:50.160 --> 28:51.540
Oh, I was sick
with food poisoning

28:51.740 --> 28:53.210
when we watched <i>Cinderella.</i>
I think we're gonna win!

28:53.410 --> 28:55.340
- Yay!
- [laughing]

28:55.540 --> 28:57.220
- Awesome.
- Yeah, go us.

28:57.410 --> 28:59.130
Dude,
what's with <i>Sex and the City?</i>

28:59.330 --> 29:01.590
The shoes are a very important
part of the story.

29:01.790 --> 29:03.260
- Oh...
- All right.
- Okay.

29:03.460 --> 29:05.390
- Ready?
- Yeah.

29:05.590 --> 29:06.720
- Film again.
- Movie.
- Movie. Yeah.

29:06.920 --> 29:08.140
- Mm-hmm.
- [Lily] Okay, yeah.

29:08.340 --> 29:09.230
[group] Three words.

29:09.430 --> 29:11.290
- Yeah, I know.
- [Lily] First word.

29:12.540 --> 29:14.070
- [Nick] Girl.
- Uh...

29:14.260 --> 29:15.610
- <i>West Side Story?</i>
- Yes!

29:15.810 --> 29:16.780
- Yes, Santi! Yes!
- Let's go!

29:16.980 --> 29:19.280
- How?
- I pointed west.

29:19.480 --> 29:20.820
Yeah, but how did you even know
where west is?

29:21.020 --> 29:22.700
- It's west, man.
- [Jorge Sr. laughs]

29:22.900 --> 29:24.830
- We won! We won!
- [Jorge Sr.] Yay, we won!

29:25.030 --> 29:27.580
- [Santiago] Yeah!
- We won!
- Hmm.

29:27.780 --> 29:29.910
- We won.
- [laughs] We won.

29:30.110 --> 29:32.000
[laughter]

29:32.200 --> 29:34.000
- We won.
- [whoops]

29:34.200 --> 29:36.440
- Tequila.
- Let's get tequila.

29:38.650 --> 29:40.170
What are you, a mop?

29:40.370 --> 29:41.930
'Cause you just wiped the floor
in that charades game.

29:42.130 --> 29:43.890
Well, I didn't,
but apparently

29:44.090 --> 29:46.350
Lily and Santiago are amazing
together.

29:46.550 --> 29:47.600
You okay, bud?

29:47.800 --> 29:49.350
No.

29:49.550 --> 29:51.230
Do you want to talk about it?

29:51.430 --> 29:55.040
- Yeah.
- Okay, come on.

30:00.040 --> 30:01.460
What's up?

30:02.510 --> 30:06.200
Ah, honestly,
everything was cool.

30:06.400 --> 30:08.080
It's just...

30:08.280 --> 30:09.790
I'm starting
to feel uncomfortable

30:09.990 --> 30:11.210
with Santiago being here.

30:11.410 --> 30:13.040
Yeah. It's a lot.

30:13.240 --> 30:14.420
I mean, you should've seen

30:14.620 --> 30:15.880
the two of them playing
charades together, man.

30:16.080 --> 30:18.020
It was just like...
[clicks tongue]

30:20.770 --> 30:22.340
Wh-What are you doing?

30:22.540 --> 30:24.300
It's two peas in a pod,
clearly.

30:24.500 --> 30:26.300
Wow.

30:26.500 --> 30:27.890
You really are bad
at game night.

30:28.090 --> 30:30.560
Look, I wouldn't read too much
into the charades thing.

30:30.760 --> 30:32.520
Lily would stop at nothing
to win.

30:32.720 --> 30:36.060
- Mm.
- And, you know,
it makes sense to get jealous

30:36.260 --> 30:37.650
when an ex shows up, right?

30:37.850 --> 30:41.030
But, rest assured,
you and Lil are the real deal.

30:41.230 --> 30:43.820
- You think so?
- I know so.

30:44.020 --> 30:46.030
- Come on.
- Okay.

30:46.230 --> 30:47.200
[Jorge] And we got to stop
talking about this.

30:47.400 --> 30:48.280
It's getting really old.

30:48.480 --> 30:50.910
- [muffled grunting]
- I'm going. Go.

30:51.110 --> 30:53.160
[muffled chatter]

30:53.360 --> 30:54.790
Oh, oh, uh, Ashton Kutcher.

30:54.990 --> 30:57.750
- [muffled]
- [Beatriz] Ooh, ooh, better.
Oh, oh, oh!

30:57.950 --> 31:00.420
- Michael Fassbender.
Yes, yes, yes!
- Oh yeah.

31:00.620 --> 31:03.090
- Good one.
- Yes, yes! Yes, yes! Yes, yes!

31:03.290 --> 31:05.640
[laughter]

31:05.830 --> 31:07.350
- [Henry speaks muffled]
- [Lily] What?

31:07.540 --> 31:08.970
Articulate!

31:09.170 --> 31:11.450
- [overlapping chatter]
- [laughter]

31:13.030 --> 31:15.270
In the zone, <i>tía.</i>
In the zone.

31:15.470 --> 31:17.620
- Going down!
- [overlapping shouting]

31:18.710 --> 31:19.900
Be the cookie.

31:20.100 --> 31:22.320
We practiced this.
I'm never gonna forgive you.

31:22.520 --> 31:24.900
- No!
- Oh!
- How could you?

31:25.100 --> 31:26.450
- [chatter continues]
- My money's on Miles.

31:26.650 --> 31:28.660
A surgeon must have dexterity
in their face, too, yeah?

31:28.860 --> 31:32.850
I don't know.
He's been a little sloppy today.

31:34.140 --> 31:37.330
You mean,
what he said to Carmela earlier?

31:37.530 --> 31:39.340
I thought it was fantastic.

31:39.530 --> 31:43.340
Look, I don't need
any more drama in my life.

31:43.540 --> 31:45.720
I had enough of that growing up.

31:45.920 --> 31:48.260
I see them
all over there whispering.

31:48.460 --> 31:50.050
- [indistinct chatter]
- [Beatriz] Oh, no, no, no, no.

31:50.250 --> 31:52.010
They've moved on.
They're talking about Chuey.

31:52.210 --> 31:54.180
[whispers] He got
his L.A. girlfriend pregnant.

31:54.380 --> 31:56.270
- [gasps]
- [chuckles]

31:56.470 --> 31:59.230
Look, I get that
we're protective of our own,

31:59.430 --> 32:03.150
but sometimes <i>tía</i> Carmela needs
to just shut her mouth.

32:03.350 --> 32:05.190
- Mm.
- What?

32:05.390 --> 32:06.950
We can all be annoyed by her.

32:07.150 --> 32:10.320
But if she needed us,
we would be there in a second.

32:10.520 --> 32:13.080
But none of that means that
she gets to be shitty to you

32:13.280 --> 32:16.430
and your partner, who loves you
and has to sit there and watch.

32:17.680 --> 32:20.210
I like that he stood up for you.

32:20.410 --> 32:22.590
- You do?
- Yeah.

32:22.790 --> 32:25.150
And I know
that your mom would, too.

32:26.190 --> 32:28.180
[smacks lips] Look at him.

32:28.380 --> 32:29.890
He's a keeper.

32:30.090 --> 32:32.010
[chuckles softly]

32:32.210 --> 32:34.520
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah, he is.

32:34.720 --> 32:37.350
- [Chuey] Come on, Diaz.
- [Gladys] There she goes,
there she goes, there she goes.

32:37.550 --> 32:39.900
- <i>Ahí, ahí, ahí.</i>
- [shrieks]

32:40.100 --> 32:42.620
[cheering]

32:44.210 --> 32:46.860
In your faces.

32:47.060 --> 32:49.320
[laughter]

32:49.520 --> 32:51.370
- [overlapping shouting]
- [groans]

32:51.570 --> 32:53.720
- Come talk to me.
- [laughter]

33:02.390 --> 33:04.420
Listen, we shouldn't have come.

33:04.620 --> 33:05.960
That's on me.

33:06.160 --> 33:08.260
But I-I don't like to see you
all tortured like this.

33:08.460 --> 33:10.130
I'm fine, <i>papi.</i>

33:10.330 --> 33:12.390
Come on, youngblood,
you're lying.

33:12.590 --> 33:15.600
I see the hurt in your eyes
when you look at her.

33:15.800 --> 33:18.810
That's how I looked at your
mother when we first separated.

33:19.010 --> 33:20.410
I know.

33:21.950 --> 33:24.900
- Come on.
- [patting on back]

33:25.100 --> 33:26.750
Let's get out of here.

33:27.790 --> 33:29.570
Yeah, that's a good idea.

33:29.770 --> 33:31.490
Cool, come on,
let's grab our coats.

33:31.690 --> 33:34.330
- Marshmallow games, right?
- Hmm. [chuckles]

33:34.520 --> 33:37.160
Okay, <i>mi gente,</i> shut your traps.
The tally's in.

33:37.360 --> 33:40.210
By a mere two points,
the winner is...

33:40.410 --> 33:43.480
- Chuey Diaz!
- [cheering]

33:44.520 --> 33:47.300
<i>¡Órale!</i>

33:47.500 --> 33:49.170
- That's right, baby!
- That's right. That's right.

33:49.370 --> 33:51.940
- Give me my belt.
- [cheering]

33:55.780 --> 33:57.390
Who's the man? Who's the man?

33:57.590 --> 34:00.530
[chatter, cheering]

34:06.080 --> 34:08.360
- Hey.
- Hi.

34:08.560 --> 34:10.700
[sighs] I'm sorry.

34:10.890 --> 34:12.360
You're sorry
because I didn't listen?

34:12.560 --> 34:13.910
You were right,

34:14.110 --> 34:15.200
and I lashed out at you,

34:15.400 --> 34:17.030
which you didn't deserve.

34:17.230 --> 34:19.500
You were just
trying to defend me,

34:19.690 --> 34:21.160
and I appreciate it.

34:21.360 --> 34:23.920
Well, I-I should've been
way more sensitive

34:24.120 --> 34:25.420
about your family dynamics.

34:25.620 --> 34:28.920
Yes, but...

34:29.120 --> 34:31.720
you reminded me that
I'm allowed to hold my own

34:31.920 --> 34:33.260
and stand up for myself,

34:33.460 --> 34:35.430
which is way easier to do

34:35.630 --> 34:38.950
with you by my side.

34:44.580 --> 34:46.440
Wait, did we just have

34:46.640 --> 34:48.650
a grossly mutual
and understanding makeup sesh?

34:48.850 --> 34:49.820
I believe we did.

34:50.020 --> 34:51.360
Maybe we should follow it up

34:51.560 --> 34:54.000
with a grossly mutual
and understanding make-out sesh?

34:55.090 --> 34:58.990
I mean, there's got to be
at least one empty room in here.

34:59.190 --> 35:00.910
[laughs]

35:01.110 --> 35:03.060
[overlapping chatter]

35:04.930 --> 35:06.580
Here's to
another fantastic party.

35:06.780 --> 35:08.170
- Yes.
- Well done.

35:08.370 --> 35:09.670
I'm worried about the dishes.

35:09.870 --> 35:12.510
Oh, hey, I wanted to thank you
for having us tonight.

35:12.710 --> 35:13.800
Uh, we've got a job
early in the morning,

35:14.000 --> 35:14.930
so we're gonna be heading out.

35:15.130 --> 35:16.760
Of course,
we completely understand.

35:16.960 --> 35:18.720
We're so happy that you came.

35:18.920 --> 35:20.560
Please know that
you're always welcome.

35:20.760 --> 35:22.640
That's kind.
Thanks again.

35:22.840 --> 35:23.930
Oh, uh, the rack got full,

35:24.130 --> 35:25.810
so I moved your coats
into our bedroom.

35:26.010 --> 35:27.350
I-I'll just go run up
and get them.

35:27.550 --> 35:28.980
Oh, no, no. Don't worry
about it. I'll go grab it.

35:29.180 --> 35:30.320
Okay, it's the first door
on your left.

35:30.520 --> 35:31.650
Cool. I'll be right back, <i>papi.</i>

35:31.850 --> 35:33.150
All right, cool.

35:33.350 --> 35:34.610
Oh, and, uh,
give Gladys my love.

35:34.810 --> 35:35.780
Thank her for me.

35:35.980 --> 35:37.530
And tell her
I'll give her a call.

35:37.730 --> 35:40.790
- Uh... Okay, stop it.
- Run. Just run, bro.

35:40.980 --> 35:42.930
[Beatriz] She's fine.

35:53.110 --> 35:54.520
Hey, Santi.

35:55.980 --> 35:57.220
Hey.

35:57.420 --> 35:59.300
You were gonna leave
without saying goodbye?

35:59.500 --> 36:01.260
I mean, things started off
a little weird,

36:01.460 --> 36:04.270
but I think we ended up
having a good time.

36:04.470 --> 36:07.480
We have this work thing
tomorrow, so...

36:07.680 --> 36:09.000
On the day after Thanksgiving?

36:10.080 --> 36:11.690
What do you want, Lily?

36:11.890 --> 36:14.990
What do I want?
What do you want?

36:15.190 --> 36:16.820
You're the one who came here.

36:17.020 --> 36:20.320
Well, it was a mistake,
which is why I'm leaving.

36:20.520 --> 36:22.510
I just want to make sure
we're cool.

36:25.180 --> 36:26.680
We're cool.

36:27.680 --> 36:30.210
If you came here
to say something, say it.

36:30.410 --> 36:33.420
What do you want me to say?

36:33.620 --> 36:35.380
That I came here
to get you back?

36:35.580 --> 36:38.550
- Did you?
- What's the point?

36:38.750 --> 36:41.010
- You're with somebody else now.
- I think I deserve to know.

36:41.210 --> 36:42.600
And I think I deserved to know
you were seeing Nick.

36:42.800 --> 36:43.810
You told me not to tell you.

36:44.010 --> 36:44.930
I mean, it was your idea

36:45.130 --> 36:46.680
not to talk about
the people we're dating.

36:46.880 --> 36:48.020
Just let me leave.

36:48.220 --> 36:49.560
It doesn't matter anymore.

36:49.760 --> 36:51.120
What doesn't matter anymore?

36:52.160 --> 36:55.030
You want to know? Fine.

36:55.230 --> 36:57.240
I was wrong.

36:57.440 --> 36:59.360
About us, about everything.

36:59.560 --> 37:01.820
The more I've dated other women,

37:02.020 --> 37:04.620
the more I've realized
they aren't you.

37:04.820 --> 37:07.160
I see you everywhere I go.

37:07.360 --> 37:10.420
At the gas station,
at the grocery store, I-I...

37:10.620 --> 37:13.520
[sighs] I can't,
I can't escape you.

37:15.100 --> 37:18.260
But you know what,
I'm finally willing to admit

37:18.460 --> 37:20.130
that I don't want to.

37:20.330 --> 37:23.720
- Santiago, I...
- Look, I hated seeing you
with him tonight.

37:23.920 --> 37:27.990
[sighs] I hated
every minute of it.

37:30.830 --> 37:32.790
Because I love you, Lily.

37:34.160 --> 37:36.610
I love you
more than I hate marriage.

37:36.810 --> 37:38.490
[softy] What?

37:38.690 --> 37:41.410
So, yeah,
I-I came here tonight because...

37:41.600 --> 37:44.170
because I want to be with you.

37:46.220 --> 37:48.300
Just say you want the same.

38:00.150 --> 38:02.800
Wait, I...

38:03.000 --> 38:05.470
I can't do this. I...

38:05.670 --> 38:07.570
No, I shouldn't have...

38:23.630 --> 38:26.280
- Jorge...
- No.

38:26.480 --> 38:28.410
I don't want to hear it, Lily.

38:28.610 --> 38:30.510
Just came
to get <i>tía</i> Anita's coat.

38:31.970 --> 38:33.500
- Please let me explain...
- No.

38:33.700 --> 38:36.560
Okay? Either you tell Nick,
or I will.

38:41.520 --> 38:43.610
[sighs]

38:43.810 --> 38:45.740
[thunder rumbling]

38:47.320 --> 38:49.140
That was weird
that Jorge and Henry

38:49.340 --> 38:50.680
didn't want to
walk back with us.

38:50.880 --> 38:52.770
They were so big
on the quad couple thing.

38:52.970 --> 38:54.410
Yeah.

38:55.750 --> 38:57.610
You're quiet.

38:57.810 --> 38:59.270
Hey, I know
game night is a big deal.

38:59.470 --> 39:00.780
I'm sorry
if I brought the score down.

39:00.980 --> 39:02.440
You know,
I can take an improv class.

39:02.640 --> 39:03.650
Watch a bunch
of Nora Ephron movies.

39:03.850 --> 39:05.590
I need to tell you something.

39:06.630 --> 39:08.720
Okay.

39:09.760 --> 39:12.000
Santiago kissed me.

39:12.200 --> 39:14.420
What? When?

39:14.610 --> 39:16.520
Like ten minutes ago.

39:17.680 --> 39:19.750
Are you for real right now?

39:19.950 --> 39:21.420
I am so sorry.

39:21.620 --> 39:24.430
I had no idea he was
gonna be there tonight. I...

39:24.620 --> 39:26.680
I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

39:26.880 --> 39:28.140
It just kind of sort of did.

39:28.340 --> 39:30.410
Well, h-how does it
just kind of sort of happen?

39:32.030 --> 39:34.980
As he was leaving,
he admitted he still loved me.

39:35.180 --> 39:37.100
Okay, you know what,
fuck that guy.

39:37.300 --> 39:39.400
- And he didn't mean
to get between us.
- Really?

39:39.600 --> 39:41.190
Because it sounds like
he kissed my girlfriend.

39:41.390 --> 39:43.250
Yes, but...

39:45.170 --> 39:47.130
I kissed him back.

39:48.470 --> 39:49.660
Fuck.

39:49.860 --> 39:51.660
- Lily.
- Look.

39:51.860 --> 39:53.160
I'm not proud of it, but...

39:53.360 --> 39:54.790
but, in the moment,
I got lost.

39:54.990 --> 39:58.040
It was a huge mistake,
and I am so sorry,

39:58.240 --> 40:00.790
and I-I needed to tell you.
I...

40:00.990 --> 40:03.840
I-I don't even know how
to respond to that right now.

40:04.040 --> 40:07.760
Nick, I am so sorry. I...

40:07.960 --> 40:09.400
You head on in.

40:10.820 --> 40:12.320
I got to take a walk.

40:13.870 --> 40:15.450
Alone.

40:33.010 --> 40:35.700
Oh, no, did somebody finish
<i>tía</i> Anita's mole?

40:35.900 --> 40:37.710
Uh, no.

40:37.910 --> 40:40.420
I accidentally threw it
in a trash bag,

40:40.620 --> 40:42.880
double-bagged it, and put it
in our neighbor's bin.

40:43.080 --> 40:44.670
[laughs]

40:44.870 --> 40:46.170
It will not be
traced back to us.

40:46.370 --> 40:48.220
Oh, God, I love you so much.

40:48.420 --> 40:50.970
[clears throat] In fact,

40:51.170 --> 40:54.600
remember when we were talking
with Jorgito earlier about vows?

40:54.800 --> 40:56.520
- Mm.
- Well, uh,

40:56.720 --> 40:58.230
I got a little something
for you.

40:58.430 --> 41:00.400
[gasps] Oh, really?

41:00.600 --> 41:03.210
- [clears throat]
- Oh.

41:05.920 --> 41:09.070
Beatriz Delgado,

41:09.270 --> 41:12.780
the first time
I ever saw you smile,

41:12.980 --> 41:14.410
you took my breath away.

41:14.610 --> 41:16.540
[sighs]

41:16.740 --> 41:18.330
And you have every day since.

41:18.530 --> 41:20.290
And every night, too,
but that's mostly

41:20.490 --> 41:22.290
because your elbow keeps
finding its way into my sternum.

41:22.490 --> 41:23.750
[laughs] Jorge.

41:23.950 --> 41:27.690
- And I vow...
- Mm-hmm.

41:29.070 --> 41:30.930
...to always remember
how you take your coffee,

41:31.130 --> 41:32.800
with just a drop of soy milk.

41:33.000 --> 41:35.680
To protect you from any spiders
that dare enter our home.

41:35.880 --> 41:38.060
[Beatriz laughs]

41:38.260 --> 41:40.740
To never,
ever take you for granted again.

41:43.830 --> 41:46.400
And to love and cherish you
today,

41:46.600 --> 41:49.420
tomorrow, forever.

41:50.710 --> 41:52.700
Jorge.

41:52.900 --> 41:54.580
I know, right?

41:54.770 --> 41:58.200
[both laugh]

41:58.400 --> 42:00.790
Okay, um...

42:00.990 --> 42:04.330
I did not get to plan ahead,

42:04.530 --> 42:06.670
but, uh,
let me take a swing at it.

42:06.870 --> 42:08.670
Oh. [clears throat]

42:08.870 --> 42:10.720
- <i>Ándale.</i>
- Okay.

42:10.920 --> 42:12.430
[clears throat]

42:12.630 --> 42:15.010
Jorge Diaz.

42:15.210 --> 42:19.980
The first time
you ever said I love you,

42:20.170 --> 42:22.100
you made me weak in the knees.

42:22.300 --> 42:26.360
And it still does to this day.

42:26.560 --> 42:31.990
And I-I can't believe
how lucky I am

42:32.190 --> 42:36.490
that I get to wake up
to this hunk of a man

42:36.690 --> 42:38.290
[laughs] every single morning.

42:38.480 --> 42:40.120
Morning breath and all.

42:40.320 --> 42:42.080
Oh, well, hey,
the tongue scraper helps.

42:42.280 --> 42:43.830
No, it really has.

42:44.030 --> 42:46.000
Ooh, ooh.

42:46.200 --> 42:49.880
I vow to always protect you

42:50.080 --> 42:51.880
from <i>tío</i> Quique's
latest pyramid scheme.

42:52.080 --> 42:53.510
[laughs]

42:53.710 --> 42:58.180
And to always save you
the last piece of flan.

42:58.380 --> 43:02.870
And to love and cherish you...

43:04.660 --> 43:09.040
...today, tomorrow, forever.

43:13.590 --> 43:15.280
Well, what are you waiting for?

43:15.480 --> 43:17.890
Are you gonna kiss the bride
or what?

43:18.090 --> 43:23.660
♪ <i>Whenever I'm alone with you</i> ♪

43:23.860 --> 43:25.480
Mmm.

43:25.680 --> 43:28.340
- ♪ <i>You make me feel...</i>
- [giggles softly]

43:28.530 --> 43:30.250
Happy Thanksgiving, <i>guapo.</i>

43:30.450 --> 43:32.920
No. Happy Turkey Day,
<i>mi corazón.</i>

43:33.120 --> 43:35.260
[both laugh]

43:35.460 --> 43:37.340
Oh. [sighs]

43:37.540 --> 43:41.220
♪ <i>Whenever I'm alone with you</i> ♪

43:41.420 --> 43:44.310
[rain falling outside]

43:44.510 --> 43:50.670
♪ <i>You make me feel like</i>
<i>I am fun again</i> ♪

43:53.880 --> 43:58.320
♪ <i>However far away</i> ♪

43:58.520 --> 44:02.540
♪ <i>I will always love you</i> ♪

44:02.740 --> 44:06.870
♪ <i>However long I stay</i> ♪

44:07.070 --> 44:10.750
♪ <i>I will always love you</i> ♪

44:10.950 --> 44:14.340
- ♪ <i>Whatever words I say</i> ♪
- [laughs]

44:14.540 --> 44:16.090
Mmm.

44:16.290 --> 44:20.100
♪ <i>I will always love you</i> ♪

44:20.290 --> 44:25.740
♪ <i>I will always</i>
<i>love you</i> ♪

44:29.830 --> 44:34.630
♪ <i>Yeah, I'll always love you</i> ♪

44:38.630 --> 44:44.550
♪ <i>I will always love you</i> ♪♪

44:56.440 --> 44:57.510
Hey.

44:57.710 --> 44:59.720
I'm sorry, I was just leaving.

44:59.920 --> 45:01.510
No, don't.

45:01.710 --> 45:04.180
I'm ready to talk.

45:04.380 --> 45:06.930
[shaky breath] Okay.

45:07.130 --> 45:09.770
I'm not gonna lie,

45:09.970 --> 45:12.860
it really hurts knowing that

45:13.060 --> 45:15.940
you definitely still have
some feelings for Santiago.

45:16.140 --> 45:19.170
- I didn't think I...
- But that's the thing.

45:21.340 --> 45:24.080
I understand how complicated
this whole thing has been

45:24.280 --> 45:25.830
and the history that
you two have together.

45:26.030 --> 45:27.720
I don't like it.

45:28.810 --> 45:29.920
But I get it.

45:30.110 --> 45:32.540
That's incredibly
understanding of you.

45:32.740 --> 45:36.560
And, uh, now
I'm just gonna need the truth.

45:38.570 --> 45:43.890
So I need you to be
completely honest,

45:44.090 --> 45:45.360
not just with me...

45:47.530 --> 45:49.240
...but with yourself.

45:50.330 --> 45:53.940
Who do you want
to be with, Lily?

45:54.140 --> 45:56.080
[shaky breath]

45:58.250 --> 46:00.460
I want to be with you.

46:02.710 --> 46:03.740
Why?

46:03.940 --> 46:06.180
Because you're my best friend.

46:07.840 --> 46:09.700
Because you make me feel

46:09.900 --> 46:11.830
like the person
I've always wanted to be.

46:12.030 --> 46:16.550
And maybe we're not ready
to move into a house together,

46:16.740 --> 46:18.590
but I know you feel like home.

46:18.790 --> 46:21.260
That's a good start.
Keep saying words.

46:21.460 --> 46:23.180
I've known you for forever.

46:23.380 --> 46:25.050
You've consistently
been there for me,

46:25.250 --> 46:26.560
without hesitation.

46:26.750 --> 46:28.720
You want what I want.

46:28.920 --> 46:31.390
And more than that,

46:31.590 --> 46:34.560
you don't make me feel bad
for wanting it.

46:34.760 --> 46:36.830
[sobs] I want you, Nick.

46:38.040 --> 46:41.040
Even if that means not being
friends with Santiago anymore?

46:42.340 --> 46:44.530
'Cause now that's
what I'm gonna need.

46:44.730 --> 46:47.740
- Yes.
- Okay.

46:47.940 --> 46:50.620
Okay. Okay. Yeah. [chuckles]

46:50.820 --> 46:53.330
Wait. Really? That's it?

46:53.530 --> 46:54.790
Yeah, yeah.

46:54.990 --> 46:56.920
[sighs] We're okay?

46:57.120 --> 47:00.630
As far as I'm concerned,
our future can start right now.

47:00.830 --> 47:04.090
- I love you.
- I love you.

47:04.290 --> 47:06.340
[breathing heavily]

47:06.540 --> 47:08.350
I love you. I love you.

47:08.550 --> 47:10.390
I love you so much.

47:10.590 --> 47:12.270
- Mmm.
- Ah.

47:12.470 --> 47:14.990
I love you.

47:21.380 --> 47:24.110
[both sigh]

47:24.310 --> 47:25.880
Want to watch <i>Top Chef?</i>

47:27.010 --> 47:28.990
Sure.

47:29.190 --> 47:32.300
- I'm gonna get some water.
- Understandable.

47:35.770 --> 47:39.000
[sighs] I'll get it set up.

47:39.200 --> 47:41.020
[groans]

48:03.000 --> 48:05.210
[sighs]

48:07.170 --> 48:08.590
[Henry sighs]

48:13.720 --> 48:15.220
What are you doing here?

48:16.640 --> 48:18.890
I'll be in the bedroom.

48:22.400 --> 48:23.860
So?

48:26.150 --> 48:27.680
I told him.

48:27.880 --> 48:29.340
And?

48:29.540 --> 48:32.010
And we had a...
we had a good talk.

48:32.210 --> 48:33.560
Define "good talk."

48:33.760 --> 48:35.770
He was very understanding.

48:35.970 --> 48:38.980
He accepted my apology,
and we're starting fresh.

48:39.180 --> 48:41.690
Wow.

48:41.890 --> 48:45.070
Well, he may have forgiven you,
but I haven't.

48:45.270 --> 48:47.150
Excuse me?

48:47.350 --> 48:50.030
I knew this was gonna happen,

48:50.230 --> 48:52.160
and I allowed myself
to get excited,

48:52.360 --> 48:54.700
but deep down I knew
you were gonna screw over Nick.

48:54.900 --> 48:57.000
Did-did you not hear me?
We're staying together.

48:57.200 --> 48:59.080
Right. For now.

48:59.280 --> 49:01.880
'Cause you're just doing
damage control. You're messy.

49:02.080 --> 49:04.050
- But I just cleaned it up.
- Oh, please.

49:04.250 --> 49:06.760
God, you're still in love
with your ex,

49:06.960 --> 49:08.510
and you're using
Nick as a placeholder,

49:08.710 --> 49:09.930
until you figure it out.

49:10.130 --> 49:12.350
That is so not fair.

49:12.550 --> 49:13.640
You don't know the full story.

49:13.840 --> 49:15.110
Then spare me.

49:17.160 --> 49:19.600
Well, I'm sorry
my first real boyfriend

49:19.800 --> 49:21.230
didn't turn into my fiancé.

49:21.430 --> 49:23.520
And I'm sorry I had
to struggle with my career

49:23.720 --> 49:26.780
because Dad didn't hand me
the keys to the family business.

49:26.980 --> 49:28.990
Everything just falls
into your lap.

49:29.190 --> 49:31.070
- [scoffs]
- So you have no idea

49:31.270 --> 49:32.820
how easy you have it, Jorgito.

49:33.020 --> 49:35.410
It must be real nice to judge
up there from that high horse.

49:35.610 --> 49:37.000
[scoffs]

49:37.190 --> 49:39.870
So the pretty, straight girl
is gonna tell me

49:40.070 --> 49:42.380
that my life is easy.

49:42.580 --> 49:44.790
That's rich.

49:44.990 --> 49:46.960
You're such a cliché, Lily.

49:47.160 --> 49:48.880
Henry was
my first real boyfriend,

49:49.080 --> 49:51.180
because every other man
that I was interested in

49:51.380 --> 49:54.640
was either a homophobe
or closeted or both.

49:54.840 --> 49:57.560
So I have had to work twice
as hard on this relationship

49:57.760 --> 49:59.890
to make it work
because, guess what,

50:00.090 --> 50:01.810
relationships are work,

50:02.010 --> 50:04.020
which you would know
nothing about.

50:04.220 --> 50:07.150
You're so wrapped up
in your fairy tale

50:07.350 --> 50:09.940
and your fantasy that
you refuse to grow the fuck up.

50:10.140 --> 50:13.870
And, guess what, Lil,
it's not cute anymore.

50:14.060 --> 50:16.530
You are not cute anymore.

50:16.730 --> 50:20.160
Oh, says the precious baby boy
who can do no wrong.

50:20.360 --> 50:23.380
I've literally been
the grown -up our entire life,

50:23.570 --> 50:25.420
taking care of you!

50:25.620 --> 50:27.800
I'd appreciate
a little grace as a sister,

50:28.000 --> 50:30.550
who was in the bathroom
with you picking up the pieces

50:30.750 --> 50:32.340
every time you had boy issues.

50:32.540 --> 50:34.970
You know, it-it's good
to know the kind of person

50:35.170 --> 50:37.850
my brother is now that
the bad shoe is on my foot.

50:38.050 --> 50:40.430
This isn't some random boy,
Lily.

50:40.630 --> 50:42.540
Nick is my best friend!

50:44.080 --> 50:46.820
Do you really not see
how this is different?

50:47.010 --> 50:49.070
I don't think
that you fully grasped

50:49.270 --> 50:52.610
how big of a deal this is.

50:52.810 --> 50:55.200
Your mess,
it doesn't just affect you.

50:55.400 --> 50:56.740
It affects me, too!

50:56.940 --> 51:01.250
And when you fuck this up,
which you inevitably will,

51:01.450 --> 51:04.460
we'll all be
cleaning up the mess, forever.

51:04.660 --> 51:06.500
So, Nick may trust you--

51:06.700 --> 51:09.210
congratu-fucking-lations--
but I don't.

51:09.410 --> 51:12.400
- Fuck you.
- Yeah. Fuck you.

51:16.150 --> 51:17.610
[door slams]

